Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.52,0:00:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.67,0:00:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good morning and welcome to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.81,0:00:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Auto Layout techniques in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.02,0:00:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Builder.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.73,0:00:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Jonathon Mah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.06,0:00:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm an engineer on the Interface
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.52,0:00:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Builder team, and I'll be joined
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.03,0:00:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,onstage shortly by my colleague
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.18,0:00:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Jason Yao.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.51,0:00:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In this session, we'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.06,0:00:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,starting with a partly built iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.58,0:00:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,app and use that to demonstrate
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.84,0:00:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a series of layout and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.63,0:00:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.17,0:00:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it seems like every few
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.51,0:00:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,months there's a new app to help
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.83,0:00:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,people find dates, and this is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:00:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,another one of those months.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.79,0:01:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the app we're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.55,0:01:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,starting with.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.52,0:01:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Laughter ]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.52,0:01:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.44,0:01:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Like other dating apps using
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.07,0:01:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Auto Layout is about building
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.09,0:01:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,relationships, relationships
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.19,0:01:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,between views.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.14,0:01:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And building relationships does
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.20,0:01:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,take work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.63,0:01:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's the kind of work that's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.01,0:01:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,rewarding because having laid
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,out our interface using
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.79,0:01:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints, our app can scale
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.12,0:01:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,across a variety of screen sizes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.24,0:01:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and adaptations, including ones
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.80,0:01:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which might not exist yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.97,0:01:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you've never used Auto
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.95,0:01:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout before, there's some
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.89,0:01:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,great resources online and past
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.10,0:01:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,sessions from WWDCs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.58,0:01:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But today we've got a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.48,0:01:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,content to get through, so we're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.62,0:01:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,not going to cover the basics.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.86,0:01:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we have six techniques
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.60,0:01:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that we'll be walking through.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.75,0:01:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use these in your own
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.57,0:02:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,apps, either as is or combine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.83,0:02:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,them together to form a larger
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.29,0:02:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.20,0:02:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that, let's just jump
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.57,0:02:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,right into the first one, which
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.20,0:02:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is changing layout at runtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.54,0:02:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now at the top of our app we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.83,0:02:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,have a slider area where the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.74,0:02:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,user can set a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.36,0:02:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And usually, we expect the user
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.09,0:02:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to set this once and then not
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.43,0:02:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,need to change it for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.51,0:02:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'd like for this area to be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.84,0:02:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,able to collapse away and reduce
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.42,0:02:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,clutter in our interface.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.09,0:02:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if we think about this from
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.08,0:02:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a layout perspective, what we're
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.20,0:02:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to do is collapse the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.07,0:02:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,height of this area to 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.87,0:02:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if we add a height
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.73,0:02:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint and then set the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.76,0:02:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,constant to 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.23,0:02:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If we did this in Interface
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.16,0:02:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Builder, we'd get something like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.13,0:02:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.08,0:02:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we're seeing here is our
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.38,0:02:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,layout with a bunch of red lines
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.26,0:02:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,indicating that our layout
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.49,0:02:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't have a solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.77,0:02:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We have what's called a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.58,0:03:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.79,0:03:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So a conflict means that we've
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.40,0:03:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,asked the layout engine to do
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.21,0:03:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple incompatible things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.04,0:03:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, set the height of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.00,0:03:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,this area to 0 while also
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.85,0:03:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping the height large enough
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.02,0:03:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to fit the content inside of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.92,0:03:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The technique that we'll use to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.23,0:03:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,solve this is to take the view
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.89,0:03:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that contains our control, our
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.16,0:03:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,slider, and our labels, and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.70,0:03:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll wrap it in another view,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.52,0:03:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,here indicated in orange.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.33,0:03:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now instead of just collapsing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.90,0:03:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the view containing our
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.61,0:03:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,controls, we'll collapse this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.96,0:03:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,outer view.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.20,0:03:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The inner view maintains its
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.51,0:03:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,full height and satisfies all
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.08,0:03:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,its constraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.70,0:03:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But the outer view clips the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.45,0:03:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,inner view because clips
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.44,0:03:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,ToBounds is enabled.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.24,0:03:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And this gets the effect of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.47,0:03:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,hiding the interface elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.70,0:03:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how this looks in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.56,0:03:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.41,0:04:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the slider area
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.30,0:04:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,designed in Interface Builder
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.12,0:04:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,right here, and we're designing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.09,0:04:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it in the expanded state, so we
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.53,0:04:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,can work with it more easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.59,0:04:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So since it's expanded in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.81,0:04:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Builder, we'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.91,0:04:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,collapsing it at runtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.26,0:04:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll create a constraint at
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.37,0:04:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,runtime to set this, the outer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.56,0:04:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,wrapping view height to 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.75,0:04:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, at some point, in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.51,0:04:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,response to the user touching
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.02,0:04:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the button, we'll activate that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.51,0:04:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.10,0:04:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if that were the only thing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.01,0:04:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we did we'd still hit the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.03,0:04:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,conflict situation that we saw
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.42,0:04:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,before, so we'll deactivate a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.26,0:04:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,different constraint, the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.48,0:04:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,edge of the control container to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.13,0:04:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the wrapping view.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.53,0:04:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So this will allow the outer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.54,0:04:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,view to collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.29,0:04:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at the full code for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.91,0:04:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.08,0:04:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is in our view controller
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.14,0:04:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,subclass and so we have three
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.80,0:04:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.24,0:04:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Two of them are outlets to both
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.84,0:04:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that wrapping view and the lower
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.90,0:04:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint, and we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.15,0:04:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,property to store our 0 height
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.12,0:04:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.97,0:05:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In response to touching the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.69,0:05:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,button, the first thing we'll do
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.03,0:05:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is ensure that the 0 height
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.10,0:05:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint is created, if we
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.18,0:05:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't made it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And then because we want the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.61,0:05:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior to toggle between shown
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.13,0:05:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and hidden, we'll figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.88,0:05:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which direction we're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.34,0:05:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,With that done, we'll then
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.91,0:05:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,deactivate and activate the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.05,0:05:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint that we want to have
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.01,0:05:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,-- that we want to get our
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.18,0:05:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,interface into the final state.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.90,0:05:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you notice carefully,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we're deactivating one
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.16,0:05:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint before activating
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.51,0:05:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,another constraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.38,0:05:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not simply toggling both.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.71,0:05:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason for that is that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.39,0:05:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Auto Layout tries to help us
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.11,0:05:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,avoid the conflict situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.93,0:05:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, as soon as we get into
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.26,0:05:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a conflict, it'll log a message
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.18,0:05:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to the console saying hey, I've
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.82,0:05:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,detected that these constraints
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.85,0:05:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,are conflicting with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.18,0:06:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we activated, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.63,0:06:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,0 height while the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.22,0:06:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint was still activated,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.27,0:06:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd get that message.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.05,0:06:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,By deactivating first, we avoid
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.49,0:06:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.17,0:06:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what we need to get
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.03,0:06:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,our interface in the final
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.98,0:06:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,state, but we also would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.08,0:06:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,animate the results so that the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.78,0:06:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,user can see -- maintain some
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.79,0:06:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,context in the application as
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.28,0:06:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the transition happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.26,0:06:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So to do that we'll use a UIView
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.74,0:06:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,animation block, and we'll wrap
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.55,0:06:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a call to layout if needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So this evaluates the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.06,0:06:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints, gets frame values
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.05,0:06:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and applies to them to a view,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.32,0:06:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and then UIView animation will
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.20,0:06:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,capture that and animate the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.80,0:06:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,result.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're deactivating the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint and that gives us
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.86,0:06:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,this animation effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.24,0:06:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't quite the effect that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.48,0:06:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I want, but I can change that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.15,0:06:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,simply by keeping the code
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.06,0:06:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly the same and changing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.63,0:06:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,which constraint our edge
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.50,0:06:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint outlet is connected
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.73,0:06:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.85,0:07:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had said connected to the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.46,0:07:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,top constraint, then the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.68,0:07:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,animation changes and it gets
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.49,0:07:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the effect that actually I think
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.63,0:07:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I prefer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.84,0:07:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we just saw an example of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.46,0:07:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,changing the layout in our app
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.25,0:07:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,by changing the constraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.27,0:07:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's look at another way to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.44,0:07:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,change the layout, and we'll use
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.85,0:07:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that to track touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.51,0:07:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have this central card
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.33,0:07:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,area in our app, and we'd like
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.11,0:07:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it to follow a touch around the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.32,0:07:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,screen and add a little rotation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.33,0:07:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as you get close to the edge and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.50,0:07:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,snap back once you let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.12,0:07:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the view's position onscreen
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.21,0:07:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is generally defined by its
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.92,0:07:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,frame and when we're using
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.57,0:07:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints and have constraints
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.33,0:07:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to this view, the layout engine
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.31,0:07:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,owns the value of this frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.95,0:07:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So the value itself is computed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.77,0:07:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,from the constraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.73,0:07:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's another property
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.64,0:07:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that affects the view's position
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.87,0:08:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,onscreen and that is the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.47,0:08:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,transform, and this applies an
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.63,0:08:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,offset from the frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.87,0:08:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So the type of this is a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.20,0:08:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,CGAffineTransform.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.67,0:08:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And this lets us add a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.88,0:08:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,translation, a rotation, and a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.96,0:08:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,scale that gets applied after
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.08,0:08:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the frame has been computed from
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.50,0:08:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.56,0:08:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can use this to get the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.53,0:08:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,effect that we're after, and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.34,0:08:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll jump over to a demo and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.45,0:08:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,show you how it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.78,0:08:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So here is our app in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.49,0:08:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Builder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.58,0:08:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'd like to make the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.29,0:08:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,central card area move around
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.06,0:08:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with the touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.00,0:08:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I've just added a gesture
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.62,0:08:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizer, a pan gesture
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.78,0:08:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizer, from the object
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.92,0:08:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,library to this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.27,0:08:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I add a gesture
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.54,0:08:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizer, it appears at the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.06,0:08:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,top level of the scene, so
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.41,0:08:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] and in the outline
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.05,0:08:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,view.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.36,0:08:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll open the assistant editor,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.23,0:08:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can see our view
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.56,0:08:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,controller code.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.43,0:09:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll control drag from that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.10,0:09:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,pan gesture recognizer to a spot
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.64,0:09:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in our source code.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.65,0:09:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And this will let me add an
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.73,0:09:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,outlet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.36,0:09:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, in this case, I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.43,0:09:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,connect an action, and I'll call
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.50,0:09:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it panCard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.08,0:09:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll switch the type from any to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.06,0:09:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,pan gesture recognizer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.22,0:09:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the type of the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.46,0:09:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,parameter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.60,0:09:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And specifying pan gesture
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.26,0:09:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizer let's me use
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.22,0:09:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,properties of that gesture
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.23,0:09:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizer within the action
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.78,0:09:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,method.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.44,0:09:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.96,0:09:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have our method stub here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.49,0:09:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also have an outlet that's
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.08,0:09:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,connected to that card view,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.94,0:09:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which is what we want to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.43,0:09:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in this method, I'm first
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.16,0:09:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,going to ask the sender, which
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.57,0:09:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is the gesture recognizer, for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.13,0:09:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,its translation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.08,0:09:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In effect, how far the user has
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.73,0:09:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,panned or dragged.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.38,0:10:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'm going to use the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.07,0:10:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,result to apply a transform to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.57,0:10:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,this card view.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.58,0:10:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the transform's computed by
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.80,0:10:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,this helper method right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.14,0:10:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which generates both a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.17,0:10:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,translation and adds a little
