Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.07,0:10:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,exposition of the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.38,0:10:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to hit build and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.63,0:10:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,run, and we'll see how this
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.76,0:10:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.38,0:10:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.96,0:10:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have our app.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.99,0:10:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, if I touch and move, we
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.88,0:10:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,get a rotation, and it will
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.94,0:10:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,follow the touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.86,0:10:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And then if I let go, now the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.58,0:10:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,card just stays where it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.95,0:10:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're never resetting
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.31,0:10:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the transform.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.88,0:10:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just staying the last value
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.29,0:10:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that we gave it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.21,0:10:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If I touch and move again, we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.61,0:10:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,see that it will snap back to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.10,0:10:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the original position.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.39,0:10:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because the transform
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.84,0:10:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't offset from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.97,0:10:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as soon as we go back with a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.73,0:11:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,new translation, we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.62,0:11:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,be relative to the original
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.90,0:11:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.28,0:11:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'd like the card to return
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.87,0:11:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the center once we're
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.03,0:11:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,done with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.56,0:11:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we let go of the touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.32,0:11:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we can do that by looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.97,0:11:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the state of the gesture
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.48,0:11:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the same code here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.90,0:11:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, when the state is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.59,0:11:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,ended, we'll reset the transform
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.87,0:11:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the identity transform.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.84,0:11:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's build and run again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.84,0:11:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So now when we release the card
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.18,0:11:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,snaps back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.90,0:11:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, of course, we'd like to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.02,0:11:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,animate that snapping back, so
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.26,0:11:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,let's just do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.20,0:11:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the same reset to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.21,0:11:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,identity code.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.13,0:11:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm using the UIView animate
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.22,0:11:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,variant with the spring options.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.00,0:11:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So this will give us a different
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.94,0:11:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.80,0:11:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll build and run again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.44,0:12:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, if I release the card,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.44,0:12:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it will bounce back to the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,original position, and I kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.25,0:12:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,like this playful behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.52,0:12:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.68,0:12:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. Yeah, I think people are
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.79,0:12:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,going to show their friends
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.44,0:12:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.66,0:12:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think we're in a good spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.68,0:12:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.67,0:12:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we just saw that the view
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.92,0:12:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,position is a combination of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.55,0:12:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.74,0:12:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only the frame, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.26,0:12:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,derived from the constraints,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.27,0:12:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can also use the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.29,0:12:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,transform to affect where the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.67,0:12:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,view is onscreen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.64,0:12:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was just a couple lines
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.32,0:12:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of code to add this fun
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.59,0:12:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.27,0:12:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So I hope that you guys will
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.71,0:12:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,play around with that in your
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.58,0:12:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,own apps, because it's a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.84,0:12:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.07,0:12:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So transform is great for
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.21,0:12:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,temporary changes, like we saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.52,0:12:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Like tracking a touch or an
