Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.90,0:15:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,style by opening the inspector
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.88,0:15:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and selecting an appropriate
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.34,0:15:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,style.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.80,0:15:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, I'll choose
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.68,0:15:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,caption one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.89,0:15:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So this happened to correspond
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.75,0:15:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to system 12 at the default text
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.35,0:15:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,style, so our canvas looks the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.42,0:15:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.50,0:15:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do the same with the upper
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.32,0:15:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,label.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.86,0:15:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This already had a text style
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.12,0:15:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,set.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.00,0:15:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll build and run again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.91,0:15:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So this comes up and it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.55,0:15:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,looks the same because we
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.75,0:15:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't changed the text size
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.74,0:15:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.45,0:15:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we can change the text size
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.97,0:15:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,by using the settings app on the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.71,0:15:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,simulator, but it's a little
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.40,0:15:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,cumbersome to switch back and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,forth between settings and our
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.67,0:15:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.88,0:15:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want to show you another
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.92,0:15:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,way to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.63,0:15:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If I jump back to Xcode, I can
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.28,0:15:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,use the application menu to open
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.09,0:16:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,develop a tool accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.34,0:16:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.37,0:16:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, from here, I can choose to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.36,0:16:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,target the simulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.93,0:16:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the settings tab I get
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.95,0:16:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,this font size slider.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.54,0:16:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll pull up the simulator
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.88,0:16:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,side by side, and now I can
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.88,0:16:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,change this slider and see our
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.36,0:16:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,app react in real time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.71,0:16:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This makes it a lot easier to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.88,0:16:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,test dynamic type changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.52,0:16:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.30,0:16:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, if I had an iPhone
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.59,0:16:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,plugged in or set up for
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.47,0:16:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,development here, I can also
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.83,0:16:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,choose to target that connected
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.17,0:16:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.09,0:16:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see our app adjusting --
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.59,0:16:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,reacting to the font size, but
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.25,0:16:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if it gets too large then our
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.55,0:16:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,labels are running into each
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.77,0:16:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,other and overlapping.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.44,0:16:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go fix that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.30,0:16:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in Interface Builder,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.36,0:16:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,whoops, I'm going to jump back
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.82,0:16:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.34,0:16:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to get that out the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.76,0:16:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The text area, down here, the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.60,0:17:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,size of that is defined by a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.24,0:17:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,fixed height constraint
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.13,0:17:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] constant over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.65,0:17:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, instead, we'd like this
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.92,0:17:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,size to vary depending on the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.04,0:17:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,size of the labels within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.30,0:17:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the bottom label
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.22,0:17:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,constrained to the bottom and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.24,0:17:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the top constrained to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.37,0:17:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if we added a vertical
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.56,0:17:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint between the two,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.28,0:17:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,there'd be enough information to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.37,0:17:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,size this area from the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.12,0:17:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints of the labels and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.02,0:17:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the size of the labels
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.74,0:17:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.14,0:17:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.90,0:17:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll control drag from label to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.30,0:17:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,another.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.65,0:17:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can choose to add a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.04,0:17:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,vertical spacing constraint, so
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.46,0:17:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,this will keep the labels
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.28,0:17:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,separated by the same distance
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.95,0:17:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,they are in the canvas right
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.94,0:17:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.94,0:17:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I can choose to add a vertical
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.32,0:17:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,baseline standard spacing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.81,0:17:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is similar to vertical
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.70,0:17:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,spacing except UIKit will adjust
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.54,0:17:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the constant of this constraint,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.06,0:17:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on the text style and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.04,0:17:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the current font sizes of the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.39,0:17:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,labels involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.62,0:17:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll choose to add one of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.36,0:17:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,those.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.82,0:18:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I can select and remove
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.33,0:18:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the fixed type constraint and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.18,0:18:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then build and run again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.22,0:18:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So now things are looking a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.95,0:18:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,better.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.34,0:18:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Our content area is adjusting
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.08,0:18:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for larger sizes and also
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.94,0:18:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,shrinking down for smaller
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.86,0:18:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes, if people want larger
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.82,0:18:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,information density on their
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.56,0:18:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,displays.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.05,0:18:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, using two properties in the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.37,0:18:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,label inspector, both the font
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.30,0:18:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dynamic type property,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.06,0:18:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we can make our labels adjust
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.43,0:18:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamically as the font size
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.75,0:18:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And we saw using accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.29,0:18:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,inspector to test different
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.63,0:18:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.05,0:18:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a talk later this
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.83,0:18:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,afternoon, Building Apps With
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.17,0:18:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type, with a lot more
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.34,0:18:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,information, and after this
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.67,0:18:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,session, if you want to try out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.80,0:19:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,how your own apps looks, if you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.62,0:19:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,change the font size, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.81,0:19:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,also get to the setting directly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.43,0:19:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on your phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.37,0:19:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go through accessibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.51,0:19:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you get the larger accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.16,0:19:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes' option, which gives a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.65,0:19:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,large range of values for the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.27,0:19:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,type to vary on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.76,0:19:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So check that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.07,0:19:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's time to add some more
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.27,0:19:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,views to our app.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.74,0:19:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd like to bring up Jason
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.02,0:19:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to introduce you to this safe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.91,0:19:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,area.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.83,0:19:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jason.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.31,0:19:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.30,0:19:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,My name's Jason Yao.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.34,0:19:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm an Interface Builder
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.23,0:19:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,engineer, and it's a pleasure to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.53,0:19:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,be with you here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.08,0:19:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to continue on with
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.11,0:19:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,our dating app journey and talk
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.12,0:19:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,about three more techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.90,0:19:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, the first thing I want
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.45,0:19:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk to you about is what do
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.70,0:19:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you do when you got a view
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.62,0:19:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,controller and you've got a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.64,0:19:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation bar and a tab bar and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.81,0:20:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to make sure your views
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.59,0:20:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,are positioned so that they're
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.88,0:20:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,not covered up by those bars?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.35,0:20:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As you may have heard, there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.92,0:20:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,new layout guide on iOS 11
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.17,0:20:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,called the Safe Area Layout
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.38,0:20:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.58,0:20:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a new property on UIView.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.32,0:20:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It works with Auto Layout and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.89,0:20:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is is a rectangle that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.17,0:20:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is around the bars and container
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.96,0:20:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,edges and then you can constrain
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.53,0:20:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,your views as you expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.48,0:20:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had to do this thing in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.68,0:20:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the past, you may remember the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.05,0:20:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Top and Bottom Layer Guide on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.29,0:20:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,UIViewController.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.67,0:20:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are deprecated in favor of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.02,0:20:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,this new safe area.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.62,0:20:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The Safe Area Layout Guide is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.71,0:20:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,easier to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.78,0:20:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more expressive and allows
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.65,0:20:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you to do a few new things, like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.52,0:20:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to center vertically
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.06,0:20:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,between your bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.79,0:20:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And that way as the [inaudible]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.26,0:20:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the size of your height
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.36,0:20:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,changes, say if you rotate in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.03,0:20:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,landscape, your layout will
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.67,0:20:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,adjust accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.70,0:20:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Safe Area Layout Guide is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.31,0:20:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,also something that can apply to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.74,0:20:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,tvOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.23,0:21:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When you target your app and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.61,0:21:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,your content for tvOS, you're
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.40,0:21:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,going to want to fill the big
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.14,0:21:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.04,0:21:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing you have to consider
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.80,0:21:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you're going to be on a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.92,0:21:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,wide variety of displays from
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.10,0:21:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,small ones to big ones, flat
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.37,0:21:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,screens to projectors, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.83,0:21:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,need to worry, in video terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.34,0:21:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of something called the overscan
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.60,0:21:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,region.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.28,0:21:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,On some displays, my title here
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.05,0:21:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,can be cut off because it's too
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.54,0:21:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,close to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.35,0:21:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you want to adjust your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.37,0:21:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,content so that it's within the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.18,0:21:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,safe area.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.69,0:21:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Safe Area Layout Guide
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.34,0:21:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to represent this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.41,0:21:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,region in iOS 11 for your tvOS
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.06,0:21:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,storyboards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.12,0:21:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Just constrain your views to the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.56,0:21:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,content and set it into the safe
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.50,0:21:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,area and then fill the rest of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.31,0:21:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,your view with the beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.72,0:21:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,background imagery for your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.31,0:21:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,users.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.94,0:21:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really easy to enable Safe
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.81,0:21:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Area Layout Guide in iOS 11 and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.06,0:21:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Builder.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.43,0:21:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go into your storyboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.58,0:21:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,go to the file inspector, find
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.52,0:21:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that box that says use Safe Area
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.12,0:21:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout Guides and check it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.99,0:22:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen is that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.64,0:22:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the top level view of each of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.82,0:22:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,your scenes is going to have the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.32,0:22:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,new Safe Area Layout Guide, and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.64,0:22:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,then you constrain to it just
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.20,0:22:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,like you would to other things
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.29,0:22:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,inside the canvas.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.08,0:22:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The Safe Area Layout Guide is a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.63,0:22:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,new property on UIView for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.27,0:22:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping your content unobscured
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.19,0:22:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and title safe, and, if you use
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.97,0:22:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it on iOS 11 with -- for iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.45,0:22:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,storyboards, will automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.13,0:22:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,upgrade your constraints for you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.34,0:22:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,when you check that box.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.38,0:22:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you [applause] and that is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.94,0:22:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because the geometry between the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.52,0:22:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,old Top and Bottom Layout Guides
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.43,0:22:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,will match the new Safe Area
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.22,0:22:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout Guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.66,0:22:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And best of all, that also means
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.38,0:22:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,when you use Safe Area Layout
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.32,0:22:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Guides on storyboards in Xcode 9
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.03,0:22:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll make it sure it's
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.88,0:22:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,backwards deployable to previous
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.12,0:22:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,iOSs.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.52,0:22:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.35,0:22:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I want to talk about a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.45,0:22:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,layout technique for being able
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.92,0:23:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to position yourself relative to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.35,0:23:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,your superview.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.39,0:23:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is called proportional
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.47,0:23:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,positioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.27,0:23:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And the idea is say if I have a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.87,0:23:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,dates' card in my dating app and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.48,0:23:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be able to position it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.91,0:23:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about 70% down from the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.32,0:23:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,superview.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.45,0:23:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.77,0:23:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a few techniques
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.52,0:23:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,available.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.10,0:23:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The one I want to show you today
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.73,0:23:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is the idea of using a spacer
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.01,0:23:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,view.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.32,0:23:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragging out a view, just a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.10,0:23:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,normal UIView from the object
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.35,0:23:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,library.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.00,0:23:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Constraining it but not
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.28,0:23:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,rendering it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.56,0:23:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And allowing it to be the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.58,0:23:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,scaffolding for positioning your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.33,0:23:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,view in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.44,0:23:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And this technique also applies
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.08,0:23:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to other type of layouts that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.52,0:23:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,are used in proportion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.61,0:23:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's another example, where
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.10,0:23:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a landscape view, with
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.19,0:23:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a 1/5, 2/5, and 2/5 proportion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.13,0:23:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they're centered along
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.08,0:23:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,those proportions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.29,0:23:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go ahead and take a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.15,0:23:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,look at how to do this inside of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.30,0:23:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Builder.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.96,0:23:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've got a basic layout
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.82,0:24:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.52,0:24:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And, in this case here, I want
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.83,0:24:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to position my date
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.41,0:24:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,card.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.17,0:24:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's being pushed in by a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.58,0:24:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,form sheet with the modal segue.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.52,0:24:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to zoom in a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.49,0:24:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,little closer over here, and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.08,0:24:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got two elements that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.97,0:24:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,already have some initial
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.92,0:24:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.46,0:24:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a label and I've got an
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.71,0:24:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,image.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.17,0:24:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we select them both, if
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.54,0:24:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you look really carefully,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.39,0:24:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll notice that it's blue on
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.92,0:24:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the left and right edges but the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.07,0:24:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,top and bottom are red.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.99,0:24:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That means there's some work
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.83,0:24:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that we need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.03,0:24:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever you see red in the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.05,0:24:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Builder canvas, it can
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.30,0:24:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,be one or two things.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.50,0:24:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Either you have too few
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.39,0:24:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints and you're
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.17,0:24:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,ambiguous, or you have too many
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.65,0:24:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints and you're
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.29,0:24:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,conflicting.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.31,0:24:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I just set this up so I know I
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.71,0:24:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't positioned myself
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.74,0:24:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,vertically in the superview.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.21,0:24:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go ahead and do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.21,0:24:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll do it by creating the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.85,0:24:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,spacer view.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.60,0:24:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to type UIView in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.73,0:24:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the object library.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.04,0:24:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Just drag out the view and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.67,0:24:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,position it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.20,0:24:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll give it just roughly the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.59,0:24:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,place that I want to see it in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.82,0:24:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the canvas.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.22,0:24:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, let's do a few setup
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.59,0:24:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,things.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.12,0:25:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,First I'm going to mark it as
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.07,0:25:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.33,0:25:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to [inaudible] a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.54,0:25:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,layout in runtime but we don't
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.67,0:25:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,want [inaudible] and that way
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.36,0:25:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't incur the cost of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.36,0:25:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.37,0:25:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing I want to do to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.39,0:25:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize it is, in the object
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.19,0:25:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,library, rename it to spacer
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.12,0:25:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,70%.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.39,0:25:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we need to add constraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.11,0:25:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to click on the pin
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.15,0:25:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.27,0:25:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to add a top
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.40,0:25:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint, a leading
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.65,0:25:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint, and then maybe give
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.32,0:25:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it a width so I can do
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.13,0:25:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint connections to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.94,0:25:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Add that. And you can see that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.01,0:25:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it's already moved horizontally.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.61,0:25:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But we still have the top and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.76,0:25:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom edges that are still red,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.54,0:25:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's because we haven't
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.42,0:25:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,specified a height yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.81,0:25:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to make this proportion
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.95,0:25:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of the superview, so let's go
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.89,0:25:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,ahead and do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.93,0:25:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to add a equal height
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.26,0:25:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint by dragging out from
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.22,0:25:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the spacer to the superview and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.45,0:25:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,choosing equal heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.78,0:25:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's using equal heights to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.13,0:25:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,my superview, but I realize I've
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.97,0:25:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,got a navigation bar up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.14,0:25:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I actually wanted equal
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.86,0:26:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,heights to -- well, actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.65,0:26:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,let's go ahead and set the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.37,0:26:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,proportion.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.95,0:26:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thing is I'm still
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.13,0:26:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,relative to my superview, and I
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.18,0:26:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,want to be relative to my safe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.94,0:26:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,area.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.39,0:26:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And so normally you'd have to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.58,0:26:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,rebuild the constraint to do
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.80,0:26:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.01,0:26:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But I want to show you something
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.14,0:26:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,new.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.35,0:26:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go up into the attribute
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.03,0:26:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,inspector, which is a really
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.33,0:26:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful thing, and you click on
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.04,0:26:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the item, we list now the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.79,0:26:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,neighbors that you can retarget
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.62,0:26:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,your constraint items --
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.52,0:26:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.01,0:26:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And so if I hit safe area, you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.59,0:26:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,can see it's now 70% to my safe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.70,0:26:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,area.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.81,0:26:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's go ahead and align our
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.90,0:26:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.79,0:26:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I'm going to take my
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.95,0:26:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,dates' label, drag it over --
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.75,0:26:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,create a connection using
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.86,0:26:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,control drag and align it to the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.90,0:26:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.52,0:26:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I wanted [inaudible] nicely
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.10,0:26:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,along the baseline and so again,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.09,0:26:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,all I need to do is click on the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.75,0:26:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint I just added.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.07,0:26:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to the attributes inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.23,0:26:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And go ahead and set this to the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.64,0:27:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,other attribute.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.25,0:27:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The really neat thing about Auto
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.46,0:27:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout is you don't have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.51,0:27:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,just bottom to bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.61,0:27:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do something like bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.60,0:27:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to top.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.31,0:27:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, in this case, since I have a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.57,0:27:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,single line label, I'll do
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.54,0:27:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom to first baseline and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.61,0:27:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that way, now we're 70% sitting
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.80,0:27:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,right along the baseline.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.13,0:27:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's test it out in a few
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.06,0:27:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,configurations.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.84,0:27:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So iPhone seven plus portrait
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.70,0:27:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,using the device bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.43,0:27:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's take a look in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.85,0:27:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,landscape and we're 70% there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.31,0:27:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this is what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.82,0:27:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you need to do this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.73,0:27:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,proportional technique in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.11,0:27:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Builder, use spacer
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.93,0:27:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,views to be able to get you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.16,0:27:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.78,0:27:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And you be sure to mark those
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.30,0:27:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,views as hidden so that they're
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.16,0:27:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,not [inaudible] rendering but
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.19,0:27:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,are assisting you at layout to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.04,0:27:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to position your
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.96,0:27:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.35,0:27:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're doing your layout
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.65,0:27:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,programmatically, the thing you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.44,0:28:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,can use is the UILayout Guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.59,0:28:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And so programmatically, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.69,0:28:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,use this as the equivalent to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.41,0:28:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the spacer views.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.32,0:28:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Next. Let's go ahead and talk
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.20,0:28:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,about another type of view that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.56,0:28:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.40,0:28:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.39,0:28:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,show you an example of adaptive
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.93,0:28:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,layout in our dating app, where
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.42,0:28:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we've got this view of a 4 x 4
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.11,0:28:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,grid giving me a selection, and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.86,0:28:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,then it's got a label at the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.77,0:28:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.32,0:28:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I rotate my phone, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.82,0:28:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,actually going to give me
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.51,0:28:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,something a little different.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.30,0:28:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still going to give me the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.03,0:28:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,4 x 4 grid of my dates, but it's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.26,0:28:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,going to have a text view over
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.52,0:28:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.98,0:28:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go ahead and see how we
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.39,0:28:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,could do adaptive layout using
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.52,0:28:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,stack views in Interface
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.41,0:28:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Builder.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.79,0:28:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So I've got my dates
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.58,0:28:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,storyboard over here and pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.18,0:28:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,much I've got this grid with an
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.21,0:28:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,initial layout set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.16,0:28:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go ahead and first
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.29,0:29:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,expand the object outline.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.04,0:29:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hold down option and kind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.30,0:29:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of expand everything all at
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.48,0:29:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,once.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.15,0:29:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And [inaudible] give you a tour
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.72,0:29:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the setup.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.81,0:29:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a vertical stack view
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.66,0:29:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's tied with four
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.21,0:29:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints to the superview.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.91,0:29:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's got three rows,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.60,0:29:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,essentially.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.42,0:29:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The first row is a nested
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.23,0:29:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,horizontal stack view of the two
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.07,0:29:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,images.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.36,0:29:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Second row is also a nested
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.88,0:29:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,stack view of the two images.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.14,0:29:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the third row is a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.33,0:29:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,label.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.69,0:29:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can see that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.15,0:29:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,everything's kind of equally
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.09,0:29:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sized and that is because stack
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.96,0:29:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,view has these great properties
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.58,0:29:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,like alignment, distribution,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.80,0:29:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and spacing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.92,0:29:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are a lot of options
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.33,0:29:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for being able to configure your
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.06,0:29:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,layout using stack views and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.91,0:29:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,nests of stack views.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.55,0:29:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The great part about stack view
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.79,0:29:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it manages your
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.72,0:29:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints for you so there are
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.43,0:29:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,very few constraints that you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.45,0:29:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,have to add.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.42,0:29:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to find out more
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.25,0:29:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,about the other, distribution
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.50,0:29:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and alignments options, be sure
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.07,0:29:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to check out the documentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.76,0:29:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now we're using fill
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.73,0:29:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,equally to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.46,0:29:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,everything's properly sized.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.46,0:29:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's go ahead and tune this
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.78,0:29:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,closer to what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.82,0:30:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So let's first adjust for
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.36,0:30:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,spacing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.15,0:30:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to select all
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.12,0:30:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] command and select
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.19,0:30:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,all my stack views.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.69,0:30:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we're going to give it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.71,0:30:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a slightly larger spacing here
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.10,0:30:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in the attribute inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.53,0:30:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll set it to maybe 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.36,0:30:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a little too big.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.96,0:30:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So a new to Xcode 9 and iOS 11,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.84,0:30:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a standard spacing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.68,0:30:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,option that allows the system to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.53,0:30:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,choose for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.11,0:30:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to use that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.64,0:30:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you remember back to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.26,0:30:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathon's talk about dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.69,0:30:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,type, be sure to check out
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.44,0:30:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,standard spacing for vertical
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.73,0:30:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,stack views using content that's
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.86,0:30:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,using text styles and checking
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.69,0:30:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,this baseline relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.86,0:30:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get the same effect of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.12,0:30:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamic type that you just saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.82,0:30:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,For us, since we have images and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.97,0:30:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,labels, we're going to go ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.99,0:30:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and just leave it unchecked.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.73,0:30:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next thing I want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.27,0:30:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is I want to really make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.98,0:30:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,these images are square.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.86,0:30:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they may look square to you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.94,0:30:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but they really aren't, and I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.17,0:30:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,prove it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.67,0:30:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to control drag from
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.21,0:30:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the image to itself and select
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.29,0:30:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the aspect ratio constraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.83,0:30:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see when I pop this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.87,0:31:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,open it actually says a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.67,0:31:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,multiplier of 193 to 226.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.77,0:31:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go ahead and make it 1:1.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.14,0:31:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. But something didn't quite
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.52,0:31:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,happen there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.00,0:31:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing happened in canvas and,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.49,0:31:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact, my aspect ratio is red.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.73,0:31:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's worse, if you take a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.38,0:31:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,look over here, there's a little
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.13,0:31:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,red dot.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.76,0:31:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, when we click on that,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.02,0:31:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a whole bunch of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.76,0:31:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,conflicting constraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.92,0:31:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.94,0:31:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go ahead and debug
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.36,0:31:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.88,0:31:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll give you -- we'll show
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.11,0:31:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you a technique for how to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.41,0:31:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,approach this type of problem
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.89,0:31:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,within the canvas.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.07,0:31:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've got the aspect ratio and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.26,0:31:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.34,0:31:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,validate that this is the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.97,0:31:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that introduced error.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.93,0:31:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Some I'm going to go to the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.42,0:31:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,attribute inspector for the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.38,0:31:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint and then toggle the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.44,0:31:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,installed button on and off to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.26,0:31:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,see what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.39,0:31:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, when I toggle it off, my
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.97,0:31:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,issues disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.84,0:31:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I toggle it on, they
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.78,0:31:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,appear again.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.35,0:31:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But nothing's really happening
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.48,0:31:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the canvas, so the next
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.06,0:31:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,strategy I'd like to do is I
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.02,0:31:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,like to poke around in my
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.33,0:31:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.73,0:32:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thing I care about is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.20,0:32:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,probably the other red
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.42,0:32:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints that are nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.14,0:32:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go ahead and take a look
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.57,0:32:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,at the one from the outermost
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.78,0:32:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,stack view to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.65,0:32:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we uninstall that, the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.90,0:32:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,issues disappear but we're no
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.88,0:32:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,longer fitting in the superview.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.57,0:32:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But the images are nice and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.52,0:32:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,square.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.62,0:32:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's kind of an interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.81,0:32:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.16,0:32:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go ahead and do another
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.70,0:32:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.96,0:32:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to reinstall this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.10,0:32:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.03,0:32:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm going uninstall the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.58,0:32:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,trailing constraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.38,0:32:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see again we're
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.56,0:32:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,square but this time we're
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.00,0:32:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,overflowing our superview.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.92,0:32:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what's actually happening
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.28,0:32:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is that we can't satisfy both
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.19,0:32:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the aspect ratio constraint, the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.52,0:32:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,fill equally distribution on the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.43,0:32:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,stack views, and then have it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.99,0:32:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,fit into the superview.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.49,0:32:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, for my case, I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.00,0:32:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,need to fill the entire
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.73,0:32:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,superview.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.51,0:32:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What I really want is actually
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.85,0:32:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to just stick to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.23,0:32:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I uninstall this, this is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.77,0:32:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,closer to what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.27,0:32:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But supposing we rotate in a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.35,0:32:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,landscape and my height gets
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.42,0:32:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,smaller, I still want this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.83,0:32:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint so [inaudible] that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.28,0:32:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,either.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.86,0:32:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what I'm going to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.78,0:32:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to leave it installed
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.22,0:33:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and set it to greater than or
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.61,0:33:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,equal to, and then this is more
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.84,0:33:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of what I want in portrait.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.36,0:33:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go ahead back to the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.10,0:33:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,object outline and we're now
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.69,0:33:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,going to look at landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.88,0:33:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When I click the device bar on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.40,0:33:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,landscape, you can see there's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.42,0:33:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,some work that we have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.72,0:33:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.06,0:33:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing we need to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.99,0:33:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to get closer to the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.54,0:33:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,look that we were wanting.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.57,0:33:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And, if you remember, the top
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.94,0:33:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] label needs to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.71,0:33:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,disappear, and then we're going
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.95,0:33:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to eventually put a text view
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.47,0:33:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,over on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.95,0:33:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's first work on the top
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.43,0:33:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] label.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.43,0:33:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to click on it and a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.08,0:33:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,stack view -- the thing we could
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.05,0:33:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,do is we could use the hidden
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.06,0:33:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,property.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.56,0:33:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Stack view is really great with
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.15,0:33:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,hidden subviews because it will
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.00,0:33:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,also collapse their layout but
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.79,0:33:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,keep them in the arranged
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.80,0:33:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,subviews array.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.94,0:33:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we'll go over to hidden
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.37,0:33:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,property, and actually new to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.02,0:33:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode 9, we also allow you to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.04,0:33:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,vary this by size class.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.24,0:33:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you can see --
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.52,0:34:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.91,0:34:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a plus button to make
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.86,0:34:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.31,0:34:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I'm going to pop it up
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.14,0:34:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and choose any width.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.60,0:34:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this case, because it's
